**PLEASE UPVOTE IF YOU FIND MY APPROACH HELPFUL, MEANS A LOT 😊**

**Time complexity: O(2^n)**
**Space complexity: O(n)**

**Approach:**
* Subsets can be determined by trying different combinations, so we will use recursion here.
* Case1: exclude the element then include the element.
* Case2: include the element then exclude the element.
* Either of the cases can be used to solve this problem.

**Case1:**
```
class Solution {
private:
    void solve(vector<int> nums, vector<int> output, int index, vector<vector<int>>& ans) {
        //base case
        if(index >= nums.size()) {
            ans.push_back(output);
            return ;
        }

        //exclude
        solve(nums, output, index+1, ans);

        //include
