# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
For each element we need to take two decisions. Either to **take it or not to take it**, this is how we can create all the subsets.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
If an array is of 'n' size, then it must have '2^n' subsets. 
- So, the outer loop is running till '2^n' (same as 1<<n).
- We need to take decision(take or not take) for each element. As there are 'n' elements in the array, the inner loop is running 'n' times.
- In the inner loop **if (1<<j)&i is giving a set bit** then jth element is taken in the subset, otherwise it is not taken.
- at the end of the inner loop the subset is inserted in ans (**vector of vectors**) ans.
- At the end of the Outer loop ans is returned.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n*2^n)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n^2) 

