solutions.content:
**Intuition :** Total number of subsets will be 2 to the power of `n` where n is the length of the given `nums` array. So if we find all the set bits for each positions for all the number between 0 to 2 to the power of `n`, we can replace the `nums[i]` (where i is the position of the number's bit representation, if i th position is set bit or not) for each set bit positions consecutively. If we find that the i th position is set bit then we'll put nums[i] in the postion and we'll push back that into the resultant vector `res` and res vector into `ans`.

**Note :** `1<<nums.size()` == `2 to the power of n` and `i & (1<<j)` with this we are checking if the jth position is set bit or not.

